{
  "text": "When the charge carriers are far apart in different regions of the nanosphere, as in Figure 5c , they behave almost like isolated charges. Thus, it is possible to study the relative stability of electron or hole trapping sites introducing a single extra electron or extra hole in the system [CITATION_1] .",
